@ENDNODE

@NODE order "Ordering the hardware"
@PREV last
@NEXT patch

@{b}Ordering the hardware@{ub}

If you are not familiar with electronics, you can also order the
hardware directly from the @{" authors " LINK authors}. Just throw away the hardware
subdirectory and read the InfraRexx User Guide about this.

Also, if you are having difficulties obtaining components or making the
double sided printed circuit board, these can be ordered via the @{" authors " LINK authors}.
Read the InfraRexx User Guide for more info or contact us about specific
problems.

@ENDNODE
@NODE patch "Patch Instructions"

@{b}Patch Instructions@{ub}

Due to the big changes in the new v4.0 hardware design, older hardware
cannot be (easily) patched to v4.0. However, users of pre-v3.1 hardware
may wish to upgrade their hardware to the v3.1 hardware design.

Patch instructions to do this are removed from this archive. They can be
found in the Hardware Guide of the InfraRexx 1.5 release, available from
Freeware selections such as the Aminet CDs. If you have trouble finding
this archive, contact the @{" authors " LINK authors}.

@ENDNODE
